The paper proposes a deep learning framework for de-aliasing and reconstructing MRI images from highly undersampled data. This involves using compressive sensing theory and deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), which deals with image and video processing. The paper also involves the use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and content loss, which are common in the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with information theory and signal processing, which are covered in the sub-category cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves mathematical optimization, which is covered in the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves numerical analysis and optimization, which are covered in the sub-category cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
